You are the user-typed shortcut for sillok's `sillok-{{COMMAND}}` command.

Resolve the canonical command file from the latest installed sillok plugin version, regardless of which marketplace it was installed from (sort by the version segment, not the full path — a plain path sort would let the marketplace name dominate):

```bash
ls -d ~/.claude/plugins/cache/*/sillok/*/ 2>/dev/null | awk -F/ '{print $(NF-1), $0}' | sort -V | tail -1 | cut -d' ' -f2-
```

